OL,3,C'Not fit for purpose': Regulator
OL,4,Ccriticised for lack of power
OL,6,FThe Guernsey Competition Regulatory
OL,7,FAuthority (GCRA) has been called "not
OL,8,Ffit for purpose" after confusion over
OL,9,Fhow much the organisation actually
OL,10,Fregulates.
OL,12,FThe organisation is meant to protect
OL,13,Fconsumers from unfair competition,
OL,14,Fhigh prices and monopolies on the
OL,15,Fisland, and saved consumers more than
OL,16,F#13 million in 2023.
OL,18,FHowever, in recent years, the GCRA was
OL,19,Fnot involved in three major business
OL,20,Fdecisions.
