OL,3,C'Not fit for purpose': Regulator
OL,4,Ccriticised for lack of power
OL,6,FIt prompted concerns at the time from
OL,7,Fthe committee's Vice President Deputy
OL,8,FSteve Falla, who said "We have a
OL,9,Fregulator in place - the GCRA - and a
OL,10,Fcompetition law in place, and we
OL,11,Fneeded to bypass both of those to make
OL,12,Fa proposal to allow the deal go
OL,13,Fthrough.
OL,15,F"I did not think that was appropriate.
OL,16,FIf there's something wrong with the
OL,17,Fregulatory model or the law, then
OL,18,Fthat's what we should deal with - not
OL,19,Fturn a blind eye to it to allow a deal
OL,20,Fto go through."
