OL,4,Ccriticised for lack of power
OL,6,F"Since it's not been independent, the
OL,7,Fprices have just gone up and up. There
OL,8,Fhas to be a break somewhere because
OL,9,Fpeople just can't afford it."
OL,11,FGCRA previously were allowed to
OL,12,Fintervene in the energy sector, but
OL,13,FStates took that power away in 2021.
OL,15,FIt was argued that the regulator
OL,16,Fshould be only allowed to look at
OL,17,Fprice impact, without taking into
OL,18,Faccount broader considerations.
