OL,3,C'Not fit for purpose': Regulator
OL,4,Ccriticised for lack of power
OL,6,FNick believes that the GCRA not
OL,7,Fintervening when mooring fees
OL,8,Fincreased proves the organisation is
OL,9,F"not fit for purpose".
OL,11,FThe GCRA could not act on prices as
OL,12,Fthe sector did not fall under the
OL,13,Fremit of competition law.
OL,15,FThe Boat Owners Association says
OL,16,Fmooring charges were raised between
OL,17,F12% to 22% above inflation, with
OL,18,Fconcerns that boat owners could face
OL,19,Ffurther increases of 20% to 30% in
OL,20,F2026.
