OL,3,C'Not fit for purpose': Regulator
OL,4,Ccriticised for lack of power
OL,6,FHe says the level of fee increases is
OL,7,Fpushing some of his members out of the
OL,8,Findustry, believing the regulator
OL,9,Fneeds to intervene in decisions that
OL,10,Faffect industry members.
OL,12,FDeputy Aidan Matthews says "We do use
OL,13,Fthe GCRA for consumer protections, but
OL,14,Fthings like mergers are one of the
OL,15,Fmost important things that happen that
OL,16,Fthey can advise on.
OL,18,F"If we're not using the regulator for
OL,19,Fthat, then (we) do have to ask the
OL,20,Fquestion, are we using the regulator
OL,21,Fin the best way?"
